05/07/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The interior ministry will celebrate its 125th anniversary with a parade Monday (5 July).
At a special ceremony marking the occasion, President Georgi Parvanov promoted Chief Secretary Boyko Borissov from major general to lieutenant general.
Three other senior officials from the security forces were also promoted.
In other news, Sliven Mayor Yordan Lechkov has suggested the military base in Novo Selo as a possible location for a NATO base in Bulgaria.
Lechkov is a former football player and star of the 1994 World Cup Finals.
(Sega, Trud, 24 Chasa, News.bg - 05/07/04)
